description:
A vegan, plant-based version of a Filipino spicy delicacy called Bopis. FULL RECIPE BELOW

INGREDIENTS:
1 cup diced tofu
1 cup diced tempeh
1/4 cup minced garlic
2 yellow onions, peeled and chopped
2 red onions, peeled and chopped
1 tablespoon minced ginger
4 pieces bay leaves
2 long green chili pepper, minced
1 red or green bell pepper, minced
1 cup diced carrots
1 cup diced radish
1 cup minced shiitake mushrooms
1 cup minced woodear mushrooms
1 tablespoon annatto powder mixed in 1/4 cup water
2 tablespoons vinegar
2-3 tablespoons brown sugar
4-6 tablespoons soy sauce

DIRECTIONS:
Heat a medium pan over medium heat. Pour enough oil to cover the bottom of the pan.

Fry the tofu until slightly golden on all sides.

Add the tempeh and fry until golden on all sides. Pour more oil if it dried up.

Turn down the heat to low heat and add the garlic and cook until golden. Mix in the onions, ginger, chili pepper, and a few pinches of salt. Cook until the onions have softened.

Add the carrots, radish, and mushrooms. Pour the annatto powder in water. Mix well.

Season with soy sauce, vinegar, and brown sugar. Adjust seasoning to taste.

Cook for another 3 minutes and turn off the heat. Serve hot with rice.
